Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: DOOR / HATCH: BACK DOOR: DISASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

DISASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE BACK DOOR UPPER TRIM PANEL ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 4 claws and 4 clips to remove the back door upper trim panel assembly as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Order of Removal

2. REMOVE BACK DOOR SIDE GARNISH LH

(a) Disengage the claw and 3 clips to remove the back door side garnish LH as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Order of Removal

3. REMOVE BACK DOOR SIDE GARNISH RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

4. REMOVE DOOR PULL HANDLE

(a) Using a moulding remover, disengage the 4 claws to remove the door pull handle.

5. REMOVE BACK DOOR TRIM BOARD ASSEMBLY

(a) Using a moulding remover, pull the back door trim board assembly in the direction indicated by the arrow shown in the illustration until there is enough of a gap to make it possible to pull on the trim by hand.

Place Hand Here

(b) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(c) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(d) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(e) Using a moulding remover, pull the back door trim board assembly in the direction indicated by the arrow shown in the illustration until there is enough of a gap to make it possible to pull on the trim by hand.

Place Hand Here

(f) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(g) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(h) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Place Hand Here

Remove in this Direction

(i) Disengage the 7 clips to remove the back door trim board assembly as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

6. REMOVE BACK DOOR LOCK COVER

(a) Using a screwdriver, disengage the claw to remove the back door lock cover as shown in the illustration.

*a

Protective Tape

7. REMOVE BACK DOOR TRIM BOARD

(a) Disengage the 5 clips in the order shown in the illustration to remove the back door trim board.

Remove in this Direction

Click here

12. REMOVE BACK DOOR LOWER STOPPER

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

(a) Remove the bolt.

(b) Disengage the guide to remove the back door lower stopper.

19. REMOVE BACK DOOR PANEL CUSHION

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the back door panel cushion.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

20. REMOVE BACK DOOR DUST PROOF SEAL

(a) Disengage the 2 claws and guide to remove the back door dust proof seal.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the other 2 back door dust proof seals.
